### Tests du endpoint SCIM pour Microsoft Entra (Azure AD)

### 1. Obtenir la configuration du Service Provider
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/ServiceProviderConfig
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 2. Obtenir tous les schémas (incluant les customs)
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Schemas
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 3. Obtenir le schéma User
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Schemas/urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:core:2.0:User
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 4. Ajouter un schéma custom
POST https://localhost:7091/scim/Schemas
Content-Type: application/scim+json

{
  "id": "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:extension:mycompany:2.0:User",
  "name": "MyCompanyUser",
  "description": "Extension pour les utilisateurs de MyCompany",
  "attributes": [
    {
      "name": "badgeNumber",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Numéro de badge de l'employé",
      "multiValued": false,
      "required": false,
      "caseExact": false,
      "mutability": "readWrite",
      "returned": "default",
      "uniqueness": "server"
    },
    {
      "name": "accessLevel",
      "type": "integer",
      "description": "Niveau d'accès de 1 à 5",
      "multiValued": false,
      "required": false,
      "mutability": "readWrite",
      "returned": "default",
      "uniqueness": "none"
    }
  ]
}

###

### 5. Créer un utilisateur avec des champs customs
POST https://localhost:7091/scim/Users
Content-Type: application/scim+json

{
  "schemas": [
    "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:core:2.0:User",
    "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:extension:enterprise:2.0:User"
  ],
  "userName": "john.doe@example.com",
  "name": {
    "givenName": "John",
    "familyName": "Doe",
    "formatted": "John Doe"
  },
  "displayName": "John Doe",
  "active": true,
  "emails": [
    {
      "value": "john.doe@example.com",
      "type": "work",
      "primary": true
    }
  ],
  "title": "Développeur Senior",
  "externalId": "ext-12345",
  "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:extension:enterprise:2.0:User": {
    "employeeNumber": "EMP001",
    "department": "IT",
    "costCenter": "CC-IT-001",
    "organization": "Example Corp"
  }
}

###

### 6. Lister tous les utilisateurs
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Users?startIndex=1&count=10
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 7. Filtrer les utilisateurs par userName
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Users?filter=userName eq "john.doe@example.com"
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 8. Obtenir un utilisateur par ID (remplacer {id} par un ID réel)
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Users/{id}
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 9. Mettre à jour un utilisateur (PUT)
PUT https://localhost:7091/scim/Users/{id}
Content-Type: application/scim+json

{
  "schemas": ["urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:core:2.0:User"],
  "id": "{id}",
  "userName": "john.doe@example.com",
  "name": {
    "givenName": "John",
    "familyName": "Doe",
    "formatted": "John Doe"
  },
  "displayName": "John Doe - Modifié",
  "active": true,
  "emails": [
    {
      "value": "john.doe@example.com",
      "type": "work",
      "primary": true
    }
  ],
  "title": "Lead Developer"
}

###

### 10. Désactiver un utilisateur (PATCH)
PATCH https://localhost:7091/scim/Users/{id}
Content-Type: application/scim+json

{
  "schemas": ["urn:ietf:params:scim:api:messages:2.0:PatchOp"],
  "Operations": [
    {
      "op": "replace",
      "path": "active",
      "value": false
    }
  ]
}

###

### 11. Créer un groupe
POST https://localhost:7091/scim/Groups
Content-Type: application/scim+json

{
  "schemas": ["urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:core:2.0:Group"],
  "displayName": "Développeurs",
  "externalId": "grp-dev-001",
  "members": []
}

###

### 12. Lister tous les groupes
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Groups
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 13. Filtrer les groupes par displayName
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Groups?filter=displayName eq "Développeurs"
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 14. Obtenir un groupe par ID
GET https://localhost:7091/scim/Groups/{groupId}
Content-Type: application/scim+json

###

### 15. Ajouter un membre à un groupe (PATCH)
PATCH https://localhost:7091/scim/Groups/{groupId}
Content-Type: application/scim+json

{
  "schemas": ["urn:ietf:params:scim:api:messages:2.0:PatchOp"],
  "Operations": [
    {
      "op": "add",
      "path": "members",
      "value": [
        {
          "value": "{userId}",
          "display": "John Doe"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###

### 16. Retirer un membre d'un groupe (PATCH)
PATCH https://localhost:7091/scim/Groups/{groupId}
Content-Type: application/scim+json

{
  "schemas": ["urn:ietf:params:scim:api:messages:2.0:PatchOp"],
  "Operations": [
    {
      "op": "remove",
      "path": "members",
      "value": [
        {
          "value": "{userId}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###

### 17. Supprimer un utilisateur
DELETE https://localhost:7091/scim/Users/{id}

###

### 18. Supprimer un groupe
DELETE https://localhost:7091/scim/Groups/{groupId}

###

